img1 <- readGDAL("hojas1.png")
## hojas1.png has GDAL driver PNG 
## and has 200 rows and 200 columns
## Warning in readGDAL("hojas1.png"): GeoTransform values not available
image(img1, col = gray(seq(0,1, length = 256)))

variog1 <- RFempiricalvariogram(data = sp2RF(img1), bin = seq(0, 20, 0.7))
plot(variog1)

img2 <- readGDAL("pasto1.png")
## pasto1.png has GDAL driver PNG 
## and has 240 rows and 400 columns
## Warning in readGDAL("pasto1.png"): GeoTransform values not available
image(img2, col = gray(seq(0,1, length = 256)))

variog2 <- RFempiricalvariogram(data = sp2RF(img2), bin = seq(0, 30, 2))
plot(variog2)

mean(img2$band1)
## [1] 132.028
var(img2$band1)
## [1] 572.1646
hist(img2$band1, freq = FALSE, col = "pink", nclass = 100,
     main = "Histograma del campo aleatorio de pasto",
     ylab = "Densidad",
     xlab = "Valor de intensidad digital (Nivel de gris)")
lines(density(img2$band1), col = "blue", lwd = 2)

modeloExpo <- RMexp(var = 570, scale = 15/3) + RMtrend(mean = 132)
plot(variog2, model=modeloExpo)
